This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing tasks such as sentiment classification and document representation. The use of deep neural network models and attention mechanisms also suggests a focus on language processing. It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) due to the use of generative adversarial networks and deep neural network models. Additionally, the use of attention mechanisms suggests a focus on optimization and learning. The paper may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) due to the focus on document representation and classification. Finally, the use of Bidirectional Gated Recurrent Unit (Bi-GRU) suggests a focus on sequence modeling and may place the paper in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category as well.
